of the Board are to—
(a) carry out the functions of the Agency;
(b) oversee the implementation and successful operation of
the policy and functions of the Agency;
(c) review the policy and strategic plan of the Agency;
(d) provide guidance to the Director-General and staff of the
Agency;
(e) approve the annual budget and plans of the Agency;
